The paper deals with modeling cascading processes on networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper explicitly mentions the transmission of disease and spread of information as examples of cascading processes. The next likely category is cs.SOC (Computational Social Science), as the paper examines the behavior of agents in a social network. The paper also uses game-theoretic concepts to model strategic behavior, which suggests cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as another possible category. The paper also involves analyzing graphs, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to predict the behavior of agents, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible category.
